"'''The Occupation of Rhamalai'''" is a 35-page short story written by [[M. H. Watkins]] that was originally published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 13|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 13]] by [[West End Games]] in [[May]] [[1997]].

==Plot summary==
The [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]] subjugates the primitive, [[Agriworld/Legends|agrarian world]] of [[Rhamalai]]. Its [[Human/Legends|human]] inhabitants have eschewed technology of any kind. The young [[Gender/Legends|men]] of Rhamalai are conscripted into the [[Imperial Army/Legends|Imperial ranks]]. Young [[Nadra Enasteri]] must leave her ailing [[Parent/Legends|mother's]] side to work in the Imperial garrison base. The Empire, having no need for Nadra's infirm mother, [[Charis Enasteri]], schedules her to be [[Death/Legends|terminated]]. [[Denel Moonrunner]], an adventurous youth being groomed as an [[Imperial Army trooper/Legends|Imperial trooper]], decides to enlist the aid of his parents to help Nadra save her mother. The elder Moonrunners are actually [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] [[Agent/Legends|agents]] who came to Rhamalai [[Standard year/Legends|years]] ago, and have hidden technology in the countryside. Their [[Astromech droid/Legends|astromech droid]] allows Denel and Nadra to bypass Imperial security and escape with Charis. The Imperials pursue, but Charis and Nadra hide in the countryside while the Moonrunners flee aboard their hidden [[Starship/Legends|starship]].

